Gov. Ahmadu Fintiri of Adamawa on Thursday assured civil servants in  the state that non of them would be victimised for his or her role  during the   last general elections. Fintiri, who gave this assurance in Yola while addressing Permanent
Secretaries, led by the state Head of Service, Dr Amos Edgar, who paid
him a solidarity visit, however said his administration would be
resolute and firm in ensuring that things worked in the state. “In the days to come,  we will role out our policies and tell you your role,” Fintiri said. He promised to provide enabling working environment and the needed equipment for workers to discharge their duties. Earlier, the Head of Service, Dr Amos Edgar, said they were at the
Government House to congratulate the new governor, and to assure him of
their loyalty. Edgar said that they were impressed with his inaugural speech in
which he declared his commitment to the welfare of civil servants. Hinatufe Henry Solomon is a graduate of Computer Science, specialist in ICT Support Services. Henry is also proficient in use of most online journalism tools and Social media management. He currently serve as Information Technology Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network.